iii) support a leading independent player through an equity investment and long-term funding.

Environmental Social Categorization Rati:
This is a Category B project under IFC's Policy on Social and Environmental Sustainability because a limited number of specific environmental and social impacts may result which can be avoided or mitigated by adhering to generally recognized good international industry practices, guidelines, design criteria, local regulations and industry certification schemes. 
Key environmental and social risks for this project include; 
Quality, Environment and Occupational Health and Safety Management systems; 
Food Safety programs and certification at processing and commercialization; 
Organic wastewater pollution load from fruit processing operations are problematic, if untreated;
Solid waste with highly organic content; 
Packaging waste and air emissions;
Refrigerant selection (non-ozone depleting substance), ammonia (NH3) safety and hazardous waste management; 
Energy efficiency and water use;
Supply chain assessment and management;
Occupational health and safety, 
Life, fire and traffic safety; and 
Labor and working conditions

Land acquisition has been done on a willing buyer-willing seller basis, and, as such, there is no involuntary displacement. There are no indigenous peoples' ancestral lands in the area. The company is working to actively upgrade its environmental management capabilities, and will ensure that its operations meet international standards for the sector.

